	sylb:summary "このクラスは、初級（しょきゅう）後半（こうはん）の学生（がくせい）のためのクラスです。毎日（まいにち）の生活（せいかつ）でつかう日本語（にほんご）を勉強（べんきょう）します。ことばや文法（ぶんぽう）、漢字（かんじ）や会話（かいわ）も勉強します。

This course is designed for students at the upper elementary level of Japanese. The purpose of this course is to provide students with the knowledge of basic sentence structures, grammatical items and Japanese writing systems including some basic Kanji. Furthermore, students will have a chance to learn about Japanese culture and society. Towards the end of this course, students are expected to become able to conduct daily communication comfortably as well as to read and write simple sentences in Japanese.

";
	sylb:method "自分（じぶん）のことを話（はな）したり、書（か）いたりすることをたくさん勉強（べんきょう）します。聞（き）いたり、読（よ）んだりすることも勉強します。ことばや文法（ぶんぽう）、漢字（かんじ）も勉強します。

(1) To enable students to communicate with local Japanese comfortably as well as to read and write short essays in Japanese through several activities. (2) To provide students with the knowledge of basic sentence structures, grammatical items and Japanese writing system (including Kanji) to promote their language proficiency.

";
